00:13:52,534 --> 00:14:07,717
How? How are we going to do this?

174
00:14:07,717 --> 00:14:10,617
It seems to be taking care of them.

175
00:14:10,617 --> 00:14:11,877
Are you sure?

176
00:14:11,877 --> 00:14:13,638
Another jambon should be fine.

177
00:14:34,849 --> 00:14:41,066
To end up this RATS talk, I'll show you one last video where you can see the implementation of the RATS state machine.

178
00:15:35,362 --> 00:15:39,664
I'll now elaborate on another important feature of the game, stealth gameplay.

179
00:15:39,664 --> 00:15:44,746
The goal was once again to reunite all the soundtrack's elements and make them breathe

180
00:15:44,746 --> 00:15:46,847
together in an interactive way.

181
00:15:46,847 --> 00:15:51,750
Stealth sections were critical gameplay sections, and the player needed to perfectly understand

182
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,451
the situation he was in.

183
00:15:53,451 --> 00:15:57,593
In Up Like Tail, when you get caught by a guard, you have a big chance of ending up

184
00:15:57,593 --> 00:15:57,913
dying.

185
00:15:58,574 --> 00:16:03,936
So audio feedbacks were clearly important, and on top of that, for immersive reasons,

186
00:16:03,936 --> 00:16:09,018
we didn't want to avoid too much UI, so audio feedback was crucial for this.

187
00:16:09,018 --> 00:16:14,140
I now illustrate how to make the soundscape evolve around common variables.

188
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,901
Video, SFX, and music are tied to these variables,

189
00:16:16,901 --> 00:16:20,363
and they are evolving together following gameplay evolution.

190
00:16:21,420 --> 00:16:27,645
In this example, two variables are used, the level of detection by guard and closest guard distance.

191
00:16:27,645 --> 00:16:30,567
For VO, it's connected to Amicia's breathing.

192
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:34,610
When guards are getting close, she starts breathing faster, for example.

193
00:16:34,610 --> 00:16:40,154
For music, music layers are evolving following the closest guard and the level of detection.

194
00:16:40,154 --> 00:16:43,856
The closest you get to a guard, the more bars you'll have, for example.

195
00:16:44,679 --> 00:16:47,861
SFX were played on top of that for detection state change,

196
00:16:47,861 --> 00:16:52,143
with the lower bit played each time she's detected.

197
00:16:52,143 --> 00:16:54,084
It was really to underline state change.

198
00:16:54,084 --> 00:16:58,846
The idea was to make it very immersive and connected to Amicia.

199
00:16:58,846 --> 00:17:01,227
We didn't want the sounds to be UI-ish,

200
00:17:01,227 --> 00:17:05,370
we wanted them to come from Amicia emotional state.

201
00:17:05,370 --> 00:17:08,791
This allowed us to extend what was on screen

202
00:17:08,791 --> 00:17:12,613
and we were a reflection of Amicia emotional state.

203
00:17:12,613 --> 00:17:14,214
Let's have a look at the example.

